A <a href="/wiki/Special_Reaction_Teams" title="Special Reaction Teams" class="mw-redirect">Special Reaction Team</a> with an <a href="/wiki/M24_sniper_weapon_system" title="M24 sniper weapon system" class="mw-redirect">M24 sniper weapon system</a> in 2004.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><br />
A <b>sniper</b> is usually a highly trained <a href="/wiki/Marksman" title="Marksman">marksman</a> that shoots targets from <a href="/wiki/Concealment" title="Concealment">concealed</a> positions or distances exceeding the capabilities of regular personnel. Snipers typically have specialized training and distinct <a href="/wiki/Sniper_rifle" title="Sniper rifle">high-precision rifles</a>. In addition to <a href="/wiki/Marksmanship" title="Marksmanship" class="mw-redirect">marksmanship</a>, military snipers are also trained in <a href="/wiki/Military_camouflage" title="Military camouflage">camouflage</a>, <a href="/wiki/Field_craft" title="Field craft" class="mw-redirect">field craft</a>, <a href="/wiki/Infiltration" title="Infiltration">infiltration</a>, <a href="/wiki/Reconnaissance" title="Reconnaissance">reconnaissance</a> and observation techniques.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
